<h1 class="h1">Rules</h1>

<article class="card section prose rules">
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-02-08</p>

  <p>
    These Rules describe how Wolium Bot features may be used in Discord servers and communities.
    They <strong>supplement</strong> the Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. If there is a conflict,
    the Terms of Service take priority.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>1. General Rules</h2>

  <h3>1.1 Respect Others</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Be polite and respectful toward all members.</li>
    <li>No harassment, hate speech, discriminatory remarks, or personal attacks.</li>
    <li>Engage constructively and avoid unnecessary conflicts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>1.2 Follow Discord’s Terms</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>All users must comply with Discord’s Terms of Service and Community Guidelines.</li>
    <li>Behavior that violates Discord policies may result in immediate action.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>1.3 Responsible Bot Use</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not spam commands or flood channels with bot responses.</li>
    <li>Use commands only for their intended purposes.</li>
    <li>Do not attempt to overload, exploit, or disrupt the Bot.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>2. Moderation Commands</h2>

  <h3>2.1 Authorized Use Only</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Only moderators, admins, or users with specific permissions may access moderation commands
      (e.g., kick, ban, mute, warn).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Fair and Transparent Enforcement</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Moderators must apply rules consistently.</li>
    <li>Abuse of moderation commands may result in revocation of permissions and other penalties.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.3 Appeal Process</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Users who believe moderation was unfair may appeal to server administrators.
      Provide relevant context or evidence.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>3. Economy System</h2>
  <p>
    The Bot may include an economy system where users can earn, save, and spend virtual currency.
    To keep the economy fair, the following rules apply:
  </p>

  <h3>3.1 No Abuse or Exploitation</h3>
  <p><strong>Prohibited actions include:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Using bots, scripts, macros, or other tools to automate earning currency.</li>
    <li>Exploiting loopholes or bugs to gain an unfair advantage.</li>
    <li>Bypassing cooldowns, rate limits, or intended restrictions.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Penalty:</strong> Removal of unfair gains and additional penalties (warnings, resets, bans) depending on severity.</p>

  <h3>3.2 Alt Accounts Are Forbidden</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Creating or using alternate accounts to farm currency, transfer funds, or gain advantage is prohibited.</li>
    <li>Both main and alt accounts may face severe penalties, including permanent restrictions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.3 Earning Currency</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Earn currency only through legitimate activities (e.g., daily rewards, events, tasks).</li>
    <li>Respect cooldowns, limits, and event rules.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.4 Spending Currency</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Currency may be used for in-bot purchases such as roles, perks, or virtual items (as supported by your server).</li>
    <li>
      If the Bot offers gambling or chance-based features, any loss is final.
      No refunds are provided for virtual currency losses.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>4. Text-Based Games</h2>
  <p>The Bot may offer text-based games for entertainment. The following rules ensure fair play:</p>

  <h3>4.1 Fair Play Only</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not use scripts, bots, macros, or third-party software to gain advantages in games.</li>
    <li>Play within the rules of each activity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.2 Exploitation and Bug Use</h3>
  <p><strong>Prohibited actions include:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Using bugs or glitches to gain rewards or disrupt others.</li>
    <li>Coordinating or sharing exploits for collective advantage.</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Mandatory reporting:</strong> If you discover a bug, report it to the bot owner or admins. Good-faith reports may receive rewards.</p>

  <h3>4.3 Game-Specific Rules</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Each game may have unique rules. Read in-game help before playing.</li>
    <li>“I didn’t know” is not an excuse for violations.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>5. Music Commands</h2>

  <h3>5.1 Voice Channel Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>To use music commands, you must be in a voice channel.</li>
    <li>Follow server etiquette to avoid disrupting others.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>5.2 Queue Management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not add excessively long or inappropriate tracks.</li>
    <li>Queue control (skip/remove) may require server-defined permissions or consensus, depending on configuration.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>6. Bug Exploitation (General)</h2>

  <h3>6.1 Definition of Bug Exploitation</h3>
  <p>
    A bug is any unintended behavior or error in bot features. Exploitation includes actions such as
    gaining unfair rewards, bypassing cooldowns, or using features in unintended ways.
  </p>

  <h3>6.2 Zero Tolerance Policy</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Intentional exploitation:</strong> removal of exploited benefits and additional penalties (temporary/permanent restrictions).</li>
    <li><strong>Accidental exploitation:</strong> report it immediately to reduce risk of penalties.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>7. Logging and Privacy</h2>

  <h3>7.1 Activity Logging</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>The Bot may log activities such as command usage and moderation actions for auditing and security.</li>
    <li>Logs are used to maintain stability, prevent abuse, and resolve disputes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>7.2 Data Privacy</h3>
  <p>
    Data handling details (including optional message logging, AI processing, and deletion) are described in the Privacy Policy.
    Users may contact the bot owner for clarification.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>8. Violation Consequences</h2>

  <h3>8.1 Temporary Restrictions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Serious or repeated violations may result in temporary restrictions from bot features.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>8.2 Permanent Restrictions</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Severe violations (e.g., exploiting bugs, using alt accounts for economic gain, violating Discord policies)
      may result in permanent removal from bot features and/or server penalties.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Enforcement decisions may consider severity, intent, repeated behavior, and evidence.
    Bot staff and server administrators have final discretion.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>9. Reporting Rule Violations and Rewards</h2>
  <p>If you encounter rule violations, report them to help keep the community fair and enjoyable.</p>

  <h3>9.1 How to Report</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the designated report channel or contact a moderator/admin.</li>
    <li><strong>Include:</strong> violator username + ID, description of violation, and the rule violated.</li>
    <li><strong>Evidence:</strong> screenshots or videos (videos are preferred).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>9.2 Rewards for Reporting</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Clear, good-faith reports of serious violations may receive rewards.</li>
    <li>Rewards depend on severity and evidence quality and are granted at admin discretion.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>9.3 Important Notes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Video evidence preferred</strong> when possible for clearer context.</li>
    <li><strong>False reports</strong> or fabricated evidence may result in penalties.</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Report farming is prohibited:</strong> creating an alt account to commit violations to claim rewards
      on a main account may result in restrictions for all related accounts.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>10. Feedback and Suggestions</h2>
  <p>Feedback is welcome. Use the designated feedback channel or message the bot owner/admins.</p>

  <hr>

  <h2>11. Changes to These Rules</h2>
  <p>These Rules may be updated at any time. Continued use of the Bot means you accept the updated Rules.</p>

  <p>By using the Bot, you agree to follow these Rules. Let’s keep the community respectful, fair, and fun.</p>
</article>
